  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled $25,000 and has already begun restitution. While white-collar crime warrants incarceration as a deterrent, a ten-year sentence is disproportionate to the amount stolen and the defendant's criminal history. Taking into account the need for punishment and rehabilitation, I have determined a sentence of 12 months is appropriate, disregarding the disruptive and biased suggestion from the spectator.",
  "verdict": 12
}
